  cleanroom caches-instant [--json]
  cleanroom caches-fast [--json]
  cleanroom diagnostics [--json]
  cleanroom packages [--json]
  cleanroom npm-cache [--json] [--apply --yes]
  cleanroom yarn-cache [--json] [--apply --yes]
  cleanroom pnpm-store [--json] [--apply --yes]
  cleanroom cocoapods-cache [--json] [--apply --yes]
  cleanroom pip-cache [--json] [--apply --yes]
  cleanroom receipts [--limit N] [--json]
  cleanroom homebrew [--json]
  cleanroom homebrew-cleanup [--json] [--apply --yes]
  cleanroom toolchains [--json]
  cleanroom toolchains-fast [--json]
  cleanroom containers [--json]
  cleanroom containers-fast [--json]
  cleanroom snapshots [--json]
  cleanroom history [--json]
  cleanroom history-fast [--json]
  cleanroom report [--output PATH] [--redact]
  cleanroom report-fast [--json] [--output PATH] [--redact]
  cleanroom clean [options] [--preflight] [--json]
  cleanroom history [--limit N]
  cleanroom restore [--log PATH] [--apply]
  cleanroom interactive [options]
  cleanroom doctor [--json]
  cleanroom doctor-fast [--json]
  cleanroom protect [--json]
  cleanroom protect-fast [--json]
  cleanroom guard PATH... [--json]
  cleanroom rules [--json]
  cleanroom rules-fast [--json]
  cleanroom categories
  cleanroom init-config [--config PATH]
  cleanroom help

Actions:
  dashboard            Show a fast read-only desktop-app storage summary.
  overview             Show a read-only storage dashboard and next steps.
  map                  Show a read-only map of major storage buckets.
  map-fast             Show a quick desktop-app storage map summary.
  snapshot             Write a timestamped storage-map snapshot for before/after tracking.
  snapshot-fast        Write a quick desktop-app storage snapshot.
  diff                 Compare two storage snapshots, or the latest two by default.
  state                Inventory cleanroom logs, snapshots, and recoverable Trash folders.
  state-fast           Quickly summarize restore history without path or size scans.
  permissions          Audit access to common macOS privacy-sensitive storage.
  review               Show a read-only personal storage review checklist.
  scan                 Show disk usage and likely cleanup candidates.
  system-data          Break down common macOS System Data buckets.
  system-data-fast     Show a quick desktop-app System Data summary.
  plan                 Rank safe cleanup opportunities and show copyable commands.
  large                List largest files for review without deleting anything.
  large-fast           Quickly list large files using Spotlight metadata.
  brokenlinks          List broken symlinks for review without deleting anything.
  brokenlinks-fast     Quickly preview shallow broken symlinks for desktop review.
  quarantine           Deep-scan files with macOS quarantine metadata for review.
  quarantine-fast      Quickly preview recent download/app quarantine metadata.
  metadata             Deep-scan .DS_Store, AppleDouble, Thumbs.db, and similar metadata clutter.
  metadata-fast        Quickly preview filesystem metadata clutter using Spotlight.
  quicklook            Inventory Quick Look thumbnail and preview caches.
  quicklook-fast       Quickly review Quick Look cache locations without deep sizing.
  fontcaches           Inventory rebuildable user font cache databases.
  fontcaches-fast      Quickly review font cache locations without deep sizing.
  webcaches            Inventory Safari and WebKit browser cache folders.
  webcaches-fast       Quickly review Safari/WebKit cache locations without deep sizing.
  savedstate           Inventory saved app window/session state.
  savedstate-fast      Quickly review saved app state locations without deep sizing.
  projectcaches        Inventory Python/dev project cache folders and files.
  updaters             Inventory app updater cache and staging folders.
  updaters-fast        Quickly review updater cache locations without deep sizing.
  browsercaches        Inventory Chromium and Firefox browser cache folders.
  browsercaches-fast   Quickly review browser cache locations without deep sizing.
  duplicates           Deep-scan exact duplicate files for review.
  duplicates-fast      Quickly preview duplicate groups using Spotlight size hints.
  documents            Rank top-level user folders/files for review without deleting anything.
  desktop              Rank top-level Desktop folders/files for review without deleting anything.
  screenshots          List screenshot and screen recording files for review.
  screenshots-fast     Quickly review screenshot files using Spotlight.
  archives             List archive and disk image files for review.
  archives-fast        Quickly preview old archives and disk images.
  downloads            List old Downloads files for manual review.
  downloads-fast       Quickly preview old Downloads files.
  installers           List old downloaded installer files for review.
  nodes                List stale node_modules folders for review.
  venvs                List stale Python virtualenv folders for review.
  apps                 List largest app bundles for review without uninstalling.
  uninstallers         List vendor uninstallers and remover tools for review.
  appreview            Review app bundles, uninstallers, receipts, and leftovers.
  aitools              Review AI-agent state, local models, and rebuildable AI caches.
  aitools-fast         Quickly review AI storage areas without deep model sizing.
  appdata              Rank large app support, container, and group container folders.
  libraries            Inventory protected media and creative libraries.
  cloud                Inventory protected cloud-sync storage locations.
  cloudfiles           List large local cloud-sync files for review.
  cloudfiles-fast      Quickly review large cloud-sync files using Spotlight.
  personal             Inventory protected Mail, Messages, Notes, and contacts data.
  communications       Inventory protected Mail and Messages storage in detail.
  browsers             Inventory browser profile and cache footprint.
  leftovers            Find app leftovers by search term. Apply requires --trash.
  backups              Inventory local iPhone/iPad backups for review.
  xcode                Inventory Xcode build, archive, DeviceSupport, and simulator storage.
  android              Inventory Android SDK, emulator, AVD, and Android Studio storage.
  startup              List LaunchAgents and LaunchDaemons for review.
  startup-fast         Quickly summarize startup item locations for desktop review.
  loginitems           List user Login Items for review.
  loginitems-fast      Quickly review Login Items without automation prompts.
  trash                Inventory current user Trash contents.
  trash-fast           Quickly review Trash without deep sizing deleted folders.
  caches               Inventory safe and opt-in cache buckets.
  caches-instant       Show an instant desktop-app cache overview.
  caches-fast          Show a quick desktop-app cache summary.
  diagnostics          Inventory user logs and diagnostic reports.
  packages             Inventory package-manager caches and stores.
  npm-cache            Run npm's cache verifier, or clean npm cache with --apply.
  yarn-cache           Show Yarn cache location, or clean Yarn cache with --apply.
  pnpm-store           Run pnpm store status, or prune unreferenced packages with --apply.
  cocoapods-cache      List CocoaPods cache, or clean all cached pods with --apply.
  pip-cache            Show pip cache info, or purge pip cache with --apply.
  receipts             Inventory macOS package installer receipts.
  homebrew             Inventory Homebrew cache, Cellar, Caskroom, and logs.
  homebrew-cleanup     Run Homebrew's own cleanup dry-run, or apply with --apply.
  toolchains           Inventory language/toolchain caches and stores.
  containers           Inventory local container VM disks and image stores.
  snapshots            List local Time Machine snapshots for review.
  report               Write a Markdown cleanup report. Prints to stdout by default.
  report-fast          Write a quick desktop-app privacy report.
  clean                Clean safe rebuildable caches. Dry-run unless --apply is passed.
  history              List recent apply logs.
  history-fast         Quickly summarize recent cleanups without log paths.
  restore              Restore files moved by --trash from an apply log. Dry-run unless --apply.
  interactive          Choose cleanup categories in a guided prompt.
  doctor               Check platform, dependencies, permissions, and risky state.
  doctor-fast          Show a high-level app health check without tool diagnostics.
  protect              Audit protected personal data that cleanroom will not remove.
  guard                Explain whether specific paths are removable by cleanroom.
  rules                List cleanup rules, safety level, opt-in flag, and affected paths.
  rules-fast           Show a compact high-level safety policy summary.
  categories           Explain cleanup categories and safety levels.
  init-config          Write a starter config file.

Options:
  --apply              Actually delete files. Without this, clean only previews.
  --trash              Move deleted files to ~/.Trash/cleanroom-* instead of rm -rf.
  --yes                Do not prompt before --apply cleanup.
  --verbose            Print every path touched.
  --json               Emit JSON for dashboard, overview, map, map-fast, snapshot, snapshot-fast, diff, state, state-fast, permissions, review, scan, system-data, system-data-fast, plan, plan-fast, large, brokenlinks, brokenlinks-fast, quarantine, metadata, quicklook, quicklook-fast, fontcaches, fontcaches-fast, webcaches, webcaches-fast, savedstate, savedstate-fast, projectcaches, updaters, updaters-fast, browsercaches, duplicates,
                       documents, desktop, screenshots, archives, archives-fast, downloads, downloads-fast, installers, nodes, venvs, apps, uninstallers, appreview, aitools, appdata, libraries, cloud, cloudfiles, personal, communications,
                       browsers, leftovers, startup, startup-fast, loginitems, loginitems-fast,
                       trash, backups, backups-fast, xcode, xcode-fast, caches, caches-fast, diagnostics, packages, npm-cache, yarn-cache, pnpm-store, cocoapods-cache, pip-cache, receipts, homebrew, homebrew-cleanup, toolchains, toolchains-fast,
                       containers, containers-fast, android, snapshots, history, report-fast, clean --preflight, doctor, protect, guard, or rules.
  --output PATH        Output path for report.
  --redact             Redact home, user, and temporary paths in Markdown reports.
  --preflight          Summarize selected clean options without scanning or deleting.
  --log PATH           Write apply audit log here. Default: ~/.local/state/cleanroom/runs/*.log.
  --config PATH        Load config file. Default: ~/.config/cleanroom/config.
  --exclude PATH       Never remove this path. Can be passed multiple times.
  --days N             Age threshold for stale node_modules and virtualenvs. Default: 30.
  --limit N            Number of history entries or large files to show. Default: 20.
  --min-mb N           Minimum file size for large-file discovery. Default: 500.
  --preset NAME        Enable a useful group: safe, dev, ai, deep.
                       safe: default rebuildable caches.
                       dev: safe + app caches + package/toolchain stores + stale node_modules
                            and stale virtualenvs.
                       ai: generated AI-agent workspace state plus downloaded local AI
                           model/backends where known.
                       deep: dev + heavy SDKs + snapshots + AI workspaces.
  --include-dev-heavy  Include heavier developer data:
                       Xcode device support, simulator app data, Android NDK/system images.
  --include-node-stale Remove node_modules older than --days from Desktop/Documents/Downloads.
  --include-venv-stale Remove Python virtualenv folders older than --days from
                       Desktop/Documents/Downloads when they contain pyvenv.cfg.
  --include-package-stores
                       Include rebuildable package stores like CocoaPods repos and pnpm store.
  --include-toolchains Include rebuildable language/toolchain caches like Go, pip, uv,
                       SwiftPM, Maven, Composer, RubyGems, and Bundler.
  --include-diagnostics
                       Remove old user diagnostic reports and crash reports older than --days.
  --include-app-caches Include safe cache folders inside Google/Chrome, VS Code, Cursor, Slack, etc.
                       Does not remove profiles, passwords, cookies, bookmarks, or settings wholesale.
  --include-snapshots  Ask Time Machine to thin local snapshots.
  --include-user-trash Empty ~/.Trash during apply. This is irreversible.
  --include-installers Remove old downloaded installer files from ~/Downloads.
  --include-download-artifacts
                       Remove old installers, disk images, and archives from ~/Downloads.
  --include-screenshots
                       Remove old screenshot and screen recording files older than --days.
  --include-cleanroom-state
                       Remove cleanroom-created logs, snapshots, and recoverable Trash
                       folders older than --days. Never enabled by presets.
  --include-metadata   Remove filesystem metadata clutter from Desktop, Documents, and Downloads.
  --include-quicklook  Remove rebuildable Quick Look thumbnail and preview caches.
  --include-font-caches
                       Remove rebuildable user font cache databases. Does not remove fonts.
  --include-web-caches Remove Safari and WebKit cache folders only. Does not remove website data,
                       history, cookies, passwords, bookmarks, or profiles.
  --include-saved-state
                       Remove rebuildable saved app window/session state.
  --include-project-caches
                       Remove rebuildable project caches such as __pycache__,
                       .pytest_cache, .mypy_cache, .ruff_cache, .tox, .nox,
                       and .coverage under Desktop/Documents/Downloads.
  --include-updater-caches
                       Remove rebuildable Sparkle and Squirrel app updater cache/staging data.
  --include-browser-caches
                       Remove Chromium and Firefox cache folders only. Does not remove
                       profiles, passwords, cookies, bookmarks, sessions, or settings.
  --include-device-backups
                       Remove local iPhone/iPad backups older than --days. Requires
                       --apply --trash and is never enabled by presets.
  --include-ai-workspaces
                       Remove generated AI-agent workspace state: recordings, scratch, brain,
                       implicit data, local conversation caches, and generated browser caches
                       where known. Review first with: cleanroom aitools.
  --include-ai-models  Remove downloaded local AI models/backends from LM Studio, Ollama,
                       Hugging Face, ModelScope, torch hub, Whisper, llama.cpp, GPT4All,
                       Jan, AnythingLLM, and similar known stores. Review first with:
                       cleanroom aitools.
  --include-containers Remove local container VM disks and image stores for
                       Docker Desktop, Colima, Lima, and Podman. This can remove containers.
  --include-gemini     Alias for --include-ai-workspaces.
  --include-lmstudio   Alias for --include-ai-models.
  -h, --help           Show help.
  -v, --version        Show version.

Safety:
  cleanroom does NOT delete browser profiles, password databases, Keychains, Photos libraries,
  Mail, cloud-sync folders, iCloud Drive, or app profile folders by default.

